SIMPLE: worm-eaten
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worm-eaten
<hw>Worm"-eat`en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Eaten, or eaten into, by a worm or by worms; <as>as,
<ex>worm-eaten</ex> timber</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Concave as a covered goblet, or a <qex>worm-eaten</qex> nut.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Worn-out; old; worthless.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir W. Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Worm"-eat`en*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[R.]</mark></wordforms> <rj><au>Dr. John Smith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wormed</ent>⟦br⟧
